repository-code: "https://github.com/0nyr/g5k-kickstart"
abstract: >-
  g5k-kickstart is a kickstart kit for running experiment campaigns
  on the Grid'5000 testbed. It packages battle-tested operational
  knowledge as an installable Claude Code plugin with an agent skill
  covering OAR reservations, the usage policy, non-interactive SSH
  operation patterns, GNU-parallel distributed runs, monitoring, and
  storage hygiene, together with human documentation and a runnable
  example experiment demonstrating the dry-run, smoke-run, full-run
  methodology.
keywords:
  - Grid'5000
  - testbed
  - experiment campaign
  - OAR
  - GNU parallel
  - reproducible experiments
  - AI agents
  - operations research
  - research software
